                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/158.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your Department’s letter of February 26 last enclosing a memorandum from the
                    Chief of Staff in regard to the proposed Duncan Concession for a railroad in the
                    Republic of Panama.</p>
                <p>Copies of your letter and its enclosure have been forwarded to the American
                    Minister at Panama.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
